Description:
BREATHTAKING CITY VIEWS
Positioned within 5 minutes' walk of North Richmond Station and Victoria Parade trams, this former grain storehouse provides a fresh and modern aesthetic, whilst retaining an industrial warehouse feel.
The "Islington Silos" have made a defining contribution to the transformation of the once industrial hub into arguably the most sought after and trendiest suburbs in Melbourne.
Entering the apartment from the elevator, the generous entry foyer leads to an expansive open living and dining area before attention is drawn to the sophisticated and well-appointed kitchen featuring vast storage, generous bench space and top line appliances. The private balcony offers stunning views of the Melbourne CBD, with plenty of room to unwind and enjoy the company of friends.
The property includes three bedrooms; the master with walk-in robe and a fully tiled en-suite and two remaining bedrooms with built-in robes and plenty of natural light, and exceptional views.
Additional features include ducted heating and cooling throughout, video intercom entry, secure undercover car space with a substantial lock up storage cage, an entertaining area including BBQ and use of a well-equipped gym.
This property offers the very best of contemporary living; an abundance of space, light, architectural flair and urban chic and is immediately accessible to the all that Collingwood has to offer
Insights: 701/55 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 18 other 3 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
QUALITY, PRIVACY AND INNER-CITY EASE
A blissfully quiet and convenient Collingwood pocket sets the scene for this unique fifties-era home offering a ready-to-enjoy lifestyle with its generous floorplan, updated features and delightful garden surrounds. Inviting interior comprises two double bedrooms (both with built-in robes) and updated central bathroom, contemporary-style kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and big breakfast bar, light-filled lounge overlooking the private brick-paved front courtyard. Other highlights include polished hardwood floors, plus secure off-street parking and private rear courtyard garden with large storeroom. Serene, secure and brilliantly positioned, it's close to cafes and restaurants, shopping precincts, easy freeway access, trams and trains to the CBD. Move in and start living!

Description:
Incredible Views, Outstanding 'Powerhouse' Living
Set behind heritage splendour of the iconic Foy & Gibson warehouse facade, an impressive modern foyer sets the scene for this exceptional top-floor 'Powerhouse' apartment. Boasting an abundance of space and light, it features generous split-level design, exquisite parquet floors and skylit vaulted ceilings. Enjoy stunning views across Collingwood's industrial charm, lush Yarra River parklands to the majestic Dandenong Ranges from wall-to-wall glazing in an open-plan expanse that incorporates both living and dining areas, opening out to a magnificent east-facing terrace. The beautifully appointed kitchen offers immaculate granite benches and timber cabinetry. Upstairs two robed bedrooms are served in style by two luxe bathrooms, including ensuite to main, while downstairs there is 3rd bedroom/study. Only moments to Smith and Gertrude St cafes, nightspots, trams and the CBD, the long list of features also comprises a downstairs powder room, video intercom, ducted heating/cooling and lift access to tandem basement car spaces.
Insights: 38/99 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 18 other 3 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Transformed for contemporary living
Eternal charm, open design and a raft of added features define the allure of this captivating Victorian cottage delivering a light-filled lifestyle of quality, originality and city-edge practicality. Beyond its attractive rendered facade, the home's vibrant interior boasts 3 double bedrooms and deluxe bathroom complete with spa bath, spacious open-plan living/dining area complemented by a timber-bench kitchen with stainless steel appliances. Forthcoming Auction, prior offers considered.
Elevated, secluded, and boutique this 2 bedroom older style 70s apartment exudes inner city charm with its appealing location and light filled living. Located on one of Collingwood's best residential streets with easy access to Smith, Gertrude & Brunswick St - this 2nd level apartment is tailor made for great inner city living and boasts an enormous communal roof deck, ideal for taking in the city skyline and entertaining. Offering a north facing orientation with natural light from 3 aspects, the apartment comprises of a large living area, separate kitchen and meals area, central bathroom, separate W/C, 2 generously sized bedrooms (main with BIR), separate storage locker as well as its own lock up garage. An innovative place to work, this exceptional dual level property is designed with a creative commercial purpose uppermost in mind. A series of five principal rooms offers generous proportions, each complemented by reverse cycle heating/cooling, striking line, colors, tones and textures, several with fitted work stations. Staff facilities, excellent storage, roller door, deck and secure basement allocated car space with an additional storage locker further complement a vibrant, versatile building in a brilliant address close to cafes, within such easy reach of the CBD, offered with concept extension plans. Alternative uses include affordable warehousing such as car storage, the prospect of residential refinement, (subject to granting of Caretaker Permit' status) or potential use of the groundfloor as a cafe (STCA).

Description:
AUCTION THIS SATURDAY - Very large 1 bed & study apartment - Investors & First Home Owners Should Attend!
Truly a dream opportunity for those keen to live the trendy Collingwood lifestyle a literal stone's throw to some of Melbourne's best cafes and eateries, this outstanding one bedroom + study apartment combines a fantastic floorplan and impressive modern style!
A thoughtful layout allows for plenty of internal space as well as private living and sleeping zones, while stylish timber floors, stone benchtops, and quality fitting and fixtures add to its contemporary charm. The relaxed central living and meals zone is adjoined by an excellent kitchen offering up stainless steel Nobel appliances, while a terrific balcony terrace is your destination for outdoor dining.
The secluded bedroom away from the action is a fantastic size and has its own study room with a built-in desk, while the well-appointed bathroom has dual vanities, a large shower, and handy laundry facilities. Other apartment features include reverse cycle heating and cooling, intercom entry, lift access, and a secure undercover car space.
Located on the 3rd floor of a boutique and uniquely historic building which has a heritage overlay, and you're just moments to Proud Mary's, Two Birds Cafe, and other funky cafes, Smith Street shops, NMIT, parks, trams, Collingwood Station, and Eastern Freeway.

Description:
Vast & versatile with huge rooftop terrace and views
From red brick brewery to brilliant warehouse conversion; this sensational 4-level loft-style sanctuary on its own Title with no Owners Corp rises to a spectacular rooftop terrace with 360-degree views. Towering 4 metre industrial ceilings, exposed brick walls, polished concrete floors and sliding barn doors frame vast interior space redefined and fitted with an eye for cutting-edge contemporary style. Drive in to a remote-control double garage; relax in the 2-room, 2 bathroom 2nd level; spread out in the huge lounge area with stunning chef's kitchen; then entertain on the roof while taking in the amazing views. Including heating/cooling, powder rooms and laundry, this multi-storey warehouse is a versatile proposition of seclusion and security that's superbly located near Gertrude Street, Fitzroy Gardens, trains, trams and the CBD. Description:
Big surprise in Little Ox with an instant reward! 6% return
An exclusive boutique development, this third-floor Little Ox apartment packs a punch with its clever design, finest-quality features and prime Fitzroy-edge location moments from the buzz of Smith Street and walking distance to everything that counts. Deluxe interior comprises one double bedroom (with robes) and classy central bathroom, stone-top kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher, light-filled open lounge/meals area leading out to a full-width balcony with elevated views. Add to this split-system heating and cooling, quality carpets and engineered oak floors, Euro laundry, plus lift access to secure entry foyer and storage cage. Inner-city perfection and six-star efficiency, it's also close to local parks, public transport options, trendy cafes and renowned restaurants. Brilliant!

Description:
Historic Arts-precinct terrace, superb potential
Historic 'Cambridge Terrace', this refurbished dwelling (zoned Mixed Use) has brilliant scope for residential/business occupancy and extension (STCA). On a deep block bordering East Melbourne, public transport, leading cafes and restaurants, this light-filled home has a versatile floor plan incorporating two living rooms, two large double bedrooms with leafy views, kitchenette, powder room, storage area, courtyard and pergola-covered rear deck. Features include ROW access parking x 2, period detailing, air conditioning and alarm. Here is a great home, home-office or investment opportunity - the only limit is your imagination!

Description:
Magnificent Penthouse
Manhattan comes to Melbourne with this captivating converted warehouse delivering cool penthouse living with a New York state of mind. Located in the inner-city's most exciting lifestyle precinct with its myriad of cafes, bars, galleries and boutiques; this exceptional 2-level residence is set at the top of an historic Foy & Gibson building retaining its original industrial character while stylishly fitted for fabulous, functional contemporary living.
The sensational city skyline is so close it's almost touchable and is enjoyed from all living areas and the stunning entertainment terrace. Including 2 secure basement car parking spaces plus lift access; 3 enclosed bedrooms provide optimum privacy while the 2 spacious open-plan areas invite individual configuration with plenty of room waiting to be used not wasted.
Secluded indoor/outdoor entertaining in this remarkable home is unforgettable!
- 3 sizable bedrooms with built-in robes, heating/cooling
- 2 modern bathrooms (ensuite access), laundry
- Spectacular alfresco terrace boasting amazing CBD view
- Vast functional open-plan sitting/dining/living area
- Gourmet granite kitchen with Ilve/Blanco appliances
- Versatile lounge or office, wet bar/fridge
- Large store room, big lift access
- Hardwood floors, huge windows, 2 basement car spaces
NOTE: Securely leased for $932 per week until 7/1/2017
NOTE: Photos not current.
